{[#]Black sacrificed a pawn in the spirit of the Volga/Benko gambit:} 13... b5
14. Bxb5 Qa5 15. Ng3 {White seems to have a normal coordination and in the
long run, he may hope to invade the f5-square. Can you spot Black's positional
idea?} c4 $1 {Indeed, this cuts the bishop off the rest of its army, allowing
the annoying knight's intrusion to d3. Black's initiative at least compensates
for the pawn.} 16. O-O Rb8 17. Qa4 Qxa4 18. Bxa4 Nd3 19. Bb5 Ng4 20. Nge2 Nxc1
21. Raxc1 Ne5 22. b3 cxb3 23. axb3 a6 24. Ba4 Nd3 25. Rc2 f5 26. Ng3 f4 27.
Nge2 f3 28. Ng3 fxg2 29. Kxg2 Bg4 30. Nf5 Nf4+ 31. Kg3 Bxf5 32. exf5 Bxc3 33.
Kf3 Be5 34. Ke4 Rb4+ 35. Rc4 Rfb8 36. f6 Kf7 37. Kf5 Rxc4 38. bxc4 Ne2 39. Re1
Nd4+ 40. Kg4 h5+ 41. Kh3 Kxf6 0-1

