{[#]White carried out the thematic b2-b4 with incomplete development and
somewhat exposed major pieces. How would you punish that?} 16... c4 $6 {
After this cooperative move White stays in control.} (16... Nfxd5 $1 {is the
thematic and strongest answer.} 17. Nxd5 ({Or if} 17. exd5 Bf5 18. Nce4 Nxd5
$17 19. bxc5 Nc3 $1 {with deadly pins and double attacks.}) 17... Nxd5 18. exd5
Bf5 19. Qa2 Bxb1 20. Nxb1 (20. Qxb1 bxa4 $17 {pins and wins the b4-pawn.})
20... cxb4 21. axb5 Bd4 $1 22. Rd1 (22. bxa6 {offers Black a decisive attack
after} Qh4 23. Rf1 b3 24. Qd2 b2 $19) 22... b3 23. Qa4 Qb6 24. Bf1 (24. Qxd4
Qxd4 25. Rxd4 Rxe2 {leaves White's minor pieces desperately hanging:} 26. Kf1
Ra2 27. Ba3 Rxb5) 24... b2 25. Bh6 Bxf2+ 26. Kh1 axb5 $19 {Material is about
equal but White is very passive and the b2-pawn should decide the game.}) (
16... Ncxd5 17. exd5 Bf5 {more or less transposes}) ({The tempting} 16... cxb4
17. Rxb4 a5 {runs into the strong exchange sacrifice} 18. Rxb5 $1 Nxb5 19. Nxb5
$44 {with perfect stability on light squares and considerable space advantage.}
) 17. Bb2 Bd7 18. a5 $14 {With a stable advanage for White who went on winning.
} 1-0

