{[#]White seems to be quite solid and Black's a-pawn is hanging. Is there a
way for Black to take over the initiative?} 19... Nb5 $1 $15 {Spotting the
hidden consequences of the weakness on c3.} 20. Rxa6 $2 {Falling into the trap.
} (20. Bxb5 axb5 $15 21. Ra6 (21. Nxb5 $2 Bxa1 22. Rxa1 Nxd5 23. Na7 Nb4 24.
Bxb4 cxb4 25. Nc6 Qb6+ $19) 21... b4 22. Na4 c4 $15) 20... Bd4+ 21. Kh1 Nxc4
22. bxc4 Nxc3 $19 {Black simply wins a piece.} 23. e5 ({Desperation. If} 23.
Bxc3 Rb3 24. Rc1 Bxc3 25. g3 {there are a few ways of getting out of the pin.
For instance} Bd2 (25... Qc8 26. Raa1 Qh3 {also wins.}) 26. Qxb3 Bxc1 27. Qc3
Qe7 28. Qxc1 (28. e5 Qb7 $19) 28... Qxe4+ 29. Kg1 Rb8 30. Ra1 Qd4+ 31. Kh1 Rb2
$19) 23... Rb3 (23... dxe5 24. fxe5 Rb1 $5 $19) 0-1

