}) 8... b5 9. Qe2 {The most active move, threatening e4-e5.} (9. Bd3 {is best
met with} Bg4 $1 (9... Bg7 10. h3 {leads to a known tabiya in which White
keeps his space advantage with light but enduring pressure. Black faces the
usual conflict between his minor pieces, despite the queenside space.}) 10. O-O
Nh5 11. Be3 Bg7 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 {Murdzia,P (2485)-Simacek,P (2508)
