This is the modern move.} Bg7 9. h3 $5 {This plan has enjoyed a relatively
long period of popularity.} (9. e4 Bg4 {invites White to a transposition to
line 2.} 10. Qb3 {This is dubious but otherwise play does not have independent
character.} ({If} 10. Be2 {Black truly transposes to the aforementioned line
with} Bxf3 11. Bxf3 O-O 12. O-O Qe7) 10... Bxf3 11. gxf3 O-O 12. Qxb7 Nh5 {
The chronic kingside weaknesses and the delay in development weight heavier
than the material gainings.} 13. Qxa8 (13. Bg3 Nd7 14. Bxd6 Bxc3+ 15. bxc3 Qf6
16. e5 Nxe5 $17) 13... Nxf4 14. Qb7 Nd7 15. Qxa6 Ne5 16. Be2 {Foisor,M (2193)
