Qxb6 19. Nxb6 Rb8 20. Bxc4 (20. Nxc4 Nxc4 21. Bxc4 Bd7 22. Rfc1 Rfc8 $11) 20...
Rd8 21. Rfd1 Bf5 22. Be2 (22. Rac1 Nc8 $11) 22... Bc2 23. Rdc1 (23. Rd2 $6 Bb3
24. Ra3 Ne4 $1) 23... Nc8 24. Nc4 Bb3 $11 {Planning ...Bxc4 followed by ...Nd6.
}) (13. e4 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 {Kaufman,L (2329)-Ortiz Suarez,I (2588) Arlington
2014 (0-1, 65)} f5 15. Qd2 fxe4 16. Nxe4 Qb6 $132) (13. Re1 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 {
Chandran,K (2229)-Sarkar,J (2399) Greensboro 2014 (½-½, 41)} f5 15. Qd2 g5
16. Bh2 Bd7 17. a5 Qe7 18. Be2 Nc7 $11 {/\...Nb5.}) (13. a5 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 {
Kunin,V (2580)-Janse,R (2227) Vasteras 2014 (½-½, 66)} Rb8 {followed by ..
b7-b5.}) 13... f5 (13... b6 {is an important alternative preventing a4-a5 but
I find it a bit too slow.} 14. Bh2 (14. Qc2 f5 15. Rab1 {followed by b2-b4
looks a better way of taking advantage of the tempo used by Black for
